#week-title("Four", "Declaring the Focus for Year Three")

=== Core Teaching

Year Three's mineral work is broad: it encompasses the Vinegar of Antimony, the
Via Humida and Via Sicca approaches, the Secret Fire and Mineral Mercury, the
Seed of Metals, the colour stages of the long mineral work, and ultimately the
approach to the Philosopher's Stone as principle. No single student will
exhaustively cover all of this in Year Three — the tradition's mineral work is
the work of decades.

The declaration of focus is therefore both practical and philosophical. The
student chooses the primary thread of Year Three's mineral work — not to the
exclusion of the broader curriculum, but as the main through-line that will
give coherence to the year.

*Possible focuses for Year Three:*
- *Via Humida deep work:* extending the water and border preparations into
  systematic mineral dissolution and cohobation
- *Antimony as primary subject:* following the Grey Wolf tradition most
  directly, from the Vinegar of Antimony through the Butyrum preparations
- *Iron (Mars) as primary subject:* working with iron as the most accessible
  non-toxic metal through calcination, vitriolisation, and dissolution
- *Copper (Venus) as primary subject:* the verdigris preparations and the
  Venus-kingdom work

The declaration is recorded in the inner work journal alongside the Adept's
Covenant. It forms the student's Year Three operational intention — a living
document, not a rigid constraint. Year Three will revise it as the mineral
work reveals what it demands.

*Preparation for Quarter IV Gathering.* The student assembles what they will
bring: the current state of all active preparations; their metal meditation
journal; the opened Year One letter (to be read from); their declaration of
Year Three focus.

=== Topics This Week

- Mapping the scope of Year Three's mineral work
- Choosing a primary focus thread
- Recording the focus declaration as a Year Three operational intention
- Preparation for the Quarter IV Gathering

#inner-work[
  *The Declaration*

  In your inner work journal, following the Adept's Covenant, write your
  Year Three declaration of focus. Include:
  - Which aspect of the mineral work you intend to pursue most deeply
  - Why this thread calls to you (be honest — practical accessibility, genuine
    fascination, and constitutional resonance are all valid reasons)
  - What you will do if the Work reveals that you have chosen the wrong thread

  The last question is the most important.
]

